# Best Practices for Browser Automation Agents (Multilogin X & Playwright)

## Multilogin X API (Port 35000)
- Always use secure local API endpoints (127.0.0.1:35000).
- Handle API authentication and error responses robustly.
- Implement profile lifecycle management: create, start, stop, delete.
- Use context isolation for each browser profile.
- Log all API interactions for auditability.

## Playwright Automation
- Integrate playwright-stealth to bypass bot detection.
- Rotate proxies and user agents for each session.
- Use explicit waits and robust selectors.
- Avoid hardcoded credentials; use environment variables or secure vaults.
- Monitor browser events and handle exceptions gracefully.

## General
- Adhere to PEP8 and enterprise Python standards.
- Document all automation flows and configuration points.
- Ensure all scripts are idempotent and CI/CD ready.
